  <static seed="1407" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/addSubtractRationalExpressions100.pg">
    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{-\frac{t}{t^{2}-5t+6}-\frac{t}{t-2}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{t}{t-3}, t\ne 2</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {-\frac{t}{t^{2}-5t+6}-\frac{t}{t-2}} 
      \amp = {-\frac{t}{\left(t-2\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-3\right)}-\frac{t}{t-2}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{t}{\left(t-2\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-3\right)}-\frac{t}{t-2}} \cdot \frac{(t - 3)}{(t - 3)} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{t}{\left(t-2\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-3\right)}-\frac{t\mathopen{}\left(t-3\right)}{\left(t-2\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-3\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{-t-t\mathopen{}\left(t-3\right)}{\left(t-2\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-3\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{-t-t^{2}+3t}{\left(t-2\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-3\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{-t^{2}+2t}{\left(t-2\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-3\right)}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-t\mathopen{}\left(t-2\right)}}{{\left(t-2\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-3\right)}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{t}{t-3}, t\ne 2}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>t - 2</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>t \ne {2}</m>.</p>
</solution>
